{
  "text": "Patients with chronic pancreatitis and patients with chronic pain syndrome for any reason will not be admitted to the PAKMAN trial because of possible pre-existing pain and tolerance to pain medication. Moreover, patients with severe chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD, stage \u2265 III according to the Global Initiative for Chronic Obstructive Lung Disease [GOLD] criteria) [CITATION_1] , or American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) physical status classification \u2265 IV will be excluded. Furthermore, the presence of contraindication(s) to the use of IV-PCA or EDA (e.g., coagulopathies or allergies), participation in another intervention trial that interferes with the intervention or outcome of this trial, impaired mental state, or language problems will also prohibit inclusion in the study.",
